10. Pokemon Theme:

```scss
/*-- scss:defaults --*/
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Press+Start+2P&family=Roboto:wght@400;700&display=swap');

$body-bg: #f0f0f0;
$body-color: #333333;
$link-color: #3c5aa6;
$font-family-sans-serif: 'Roboto', sans-serif;
$font-family-pokemon: 'Press Start 2P', cursive;
$font-size-root: 20px;

/*-- scss:rules --*/
.reveal .slides {
  background-image: url('path/to/pokeball-pattern.png');
  background-size: 100px 100px;
}

.pokedex-entry {
  border: 2px solid #ff0000;
  background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
  padding: 10px;
  border-radius: 10px;
}

.pokemon-type {
  font-family: $font-family-pokemon;
  font-size: 0.8em;
  padding: 2px 5px;
  border-radius: 5px;
}

/*-- scss:mixins --*/
@mixin elemental-bg($color) {
  background-color: $color;
  color: white;
}
```

Now, here's a Quarto example that can be used across all themes:

```markdown
---
title: "Cross-Theme Presentation"
subtitle: "Adaptable to Any Universe"
author: "Multiversal Presenter"
format:
  revealjs:
    theme: [default, chosen-theme.scss]
    slide-number: true
    logo: path/to/your/logo.png
    footer: "Multiversal Presentations Inc."
---

## Welcome to Our Multiverse

This presentation adapts to various themes:

- LitRPG
- Dungeons and Dragons
- Star Wars
- Star Trek
- Ancient History
- Harry Potter
- Ready Player One
- The Witcher
- Dragon Ball Super
- Pokemon

---

## Key Concepts

::: {.incremental}
- Universal truths
- Parallel storylines
- Character development
- World-building techniques
:::

---

## Data Visualization

::: {.adjust}
| Dimension | Power Level | Magic Points | Technology Rating |
|-----------|-------------|--------------|-------------------|
| Fantasy   | 75          | 100          | 30                |
| Sci-Fi    | 80          | 20           | 95                |
| Historical| 50          | 60           | 40                |
:::

---

## Special Elements

::: {.medieval-box .artifact .lcars-panel .oasis-interface .bestiary .pokedex-entry}
This box adapts to the chosen theme, showcasing important information.
:::

---

## Character Classes

- <span class="jedi federation hieroglyph spell easter-egg witcher-sign power-level pokemon-type">Hero</span>
- <span class="sith klingon hieroglyph spell easter-egg witcher-sign power-level pokemon-type">Villain</span>
- <span class="dice-roll house-points">Sidekick</span>

---

## Epic Quotation

> "In every universe, courage and friendship prevail."

---

## Visual Representation

::: {.adj_center_fig}
![Multiverse Map](path/to/multiverse-map.png)
:::

---

## Conclusion

- We've explored multiple universes
- Each theme offers unique perspectives
- The core message remains consistent

---

## Questions?

Thank you for joining this multiversal journey!

```

To use this template with any of the themes:

1. Choose the desired theme SCSS file (e.g., `star-wars-theme.scss`).
2. In the Quarto markdown file, update the YAML header to include `theme: [default, star-wars-theme.scss]` (replace with the chosen theme).
3. Adjust the logo and footer as needed.
4. The content will adapt to the chosen theme while maintaining a consistent structure.

This approach allows for easy switching between themes while keeping the core content intact, making it versatile for various presentation contexts.